UNITED STATES ex rel. Nachman TOLMACH and Another, Relators-Appellants, v. Henry H. CURRAN, as Commissioner, etc., Respondent-Appellee. (Circuit Court of Appeals, Second Circuit. October 10, 1924.) No. 22. Goldfogle & Dorf, of New York City (Irving S. Dorf, of New York City, of counsel), for appellants. William Hayward, U. S. Atty., and Morris Streusand, both of New York City, for appellee.

Before ROGERS, HOUGH, and. MANTON, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Appeal dismissed in open court.
